<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,2025]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,326,151,177]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[339,594,152,177]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Empidideicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amicus">
<emphasis box="[339,594,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Empidideicus amicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is separated from its closely related species, 
<taxonomicName box="[1164,1339,152,177]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Empidideicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="matricarius">
<emphasis box="[1164,1339,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">E. matricarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by the length of the second flagellomere that is as long as or longer than first flagellomere (in 
<taxonomicName box="[1216,1391,189,214]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Empidideicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="matricarius">
<emphasis box="[1216,1391,189,214]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">E. matricarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the second flagellomere is much shorter than the first flagellomere), the deep and wide apical invagination of reservoir (narrow and shallow invagination in 
<taxonomicName box="[718,894,264,289]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Empidideicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="matricarius">
<emphasis box="[718,894,264,289]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">E. matricarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and the presence of well sclerotised plates around the genital orifice (absent in 
<taxonomicName box="[575,745,301,326]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Empidideicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="matricarius">
<emphasis box="[575,745,301,326]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">E. matricarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
